  "prompt": "Why did Johnny Cash spend time in prison?",
  "response": "Johnny Cash did not spend time in prison as an inmate. However, he did perform for inmates at various prisons throughout his career. His most famous prison performances were at Folsom Prison in 1968, which resulted in the iconic live album \"At Folsom Prison,\" and at San Quentin Prison in 1969, which produced the album \"At San Quentin.\" These performances were part of his connection to the struggles of the incarcerated and helped to solidify his image as an advocate for the underdog.",
